result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler Jonathon Meyer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tyler Jonathon Meyer is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Tyler Jonathon Meyer was found guilty of Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Defendant shall participate in any and all counseling deemed appropriate by the Division of Community Corrections.
Defendant shall abide by all other terms and conditions of probation deemed appropriate by the Division of Community Corrections.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA assessment and follow through with all recommendations thereof.

Case called at 1:36 PM.
Defendant Tyler Jonathon Meyer in court with attorney Peter B. Kelly.  Katherine M. Findley appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Attorney Kelly informs the court this matter is resolved.
Defendant withdrawals plea of "NOT GUILTY" and enters a plea of "GUILTY" to Count 1.
Court questions defendant re: plea and waiver of rights.
Court also questions attorney Kelly re: his clients plea and waiver of rights.
Parties stipulate to a factual basis.
Court finds plea and waiver is made freely, knowingly & intelligently.
Court accept plea and finds the defendant "GUILTY" to Count 1.
State moves for plea agreement of the parties.
Attorney Kelly concurs with the state.
Court grants motion of the parties and orders the defendant be placed on probation for a period of 12 month with conditions.
